{
  "plan_description": "We are to disable IPv6 forwarding by ensuring the kernel parameter net.ipv6.conf.all.forwarding is set to 0.\\nSteps:\\n1. Read the current value of the parameter from the file /etc/sysctl.d/net.ipv6.conf.all.forwarding.conf.\\n2. If the parameter is not set to 0 (i.e., the line matching the pattern does not have the value 0 after the equals sign), then we update the file to set that parameter to 0 (either by replacing the existing line or appending if absent).\\n3. Write the updated content back to the file.\\nWe use only read_file and write_file. We do not use run_cmd because we are not executing any shell command."
}
